data.description:
Table presented on the New York Times web site on March 23, 2007, accompanying this article:
http://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/23/nyregion/23cnd-schools.html
"The chart shows comparative spending per pupil in more than 600 school districts across New Jersey. Spending tends to be higher in small wealthy districts, and in poor districts that get large amounts of state money under court order, such as Newark, Asbury Park and Camden."
Variables are:
County Group Cost per pupil 2006-07 Cost per pupil 2005-06 Rank among 603 districts statewide in 2006-07 Percent funded locally Student-teacher ratio Percent special education students
